				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Just as a matter of course, the <em>default</em> thing to happen to any game is for it to fail and never come out. The games that do get released are the ones that you should wonder why they happened. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />Well over half of all commercial software projects fail, and most of them you never get to hear about. Failure is a bad look for a company, you tend to want to keep these things quiet if you can.<br /><br />The Saturn didn't do well and it only had a few years window where a new Sonic game for it was viable. They tried, and failed, and then their time was up.</div>

